<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-28T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-28T17:00:00-05:00" n="863" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d863">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00111 A.R.–Subs/16: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in El Salvador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Frazer</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">San Salvador</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-28T16:00:00-06:00">June 28,
                                    1940—4 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 7 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>30. Salvadoran decree excluding belligerent submarines and other naval
                            vessels from ports and territories promulgated June 26th.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Frazer</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>